description: Adam Peaty tested positive for COVID a day after joining American Nic Fink at a press conference after the 100 meter breaststroke final. USA Swimming say it's "taking the necessary precautions."
title: Covid hits British Olympic swimming star who had close contact with U.S. athlete

description: The U.S. women's Olympic basketball team cruised over Japan 102-76. The U.S. squad, which now boasts a 56-game Olympic winning streak, is on the hunt for an eighth-straight Olympic gold medal.
title: U.S. women’s basketball team opens the Olympics with dominant win over Japan

description: Congressional Democrats tout their favorites on Harris' short list. Sen. Tim Kaine, who was Clinton's running mate, says accelerated vetting means fewer options.
title: Democrats weigh in on Harris' pick for running mate

description: On Monday, Iowa's ban on abortions as early as six weeks takes effect — sending ripple effects on access to abortion throughout the Midwest.
title: Iowa is the latest state to impose tighter limits on abortion access

description: The U.S. women's basketball team begins its quest for an unprecedented eighth straight Olympic gold medal. The squad opens at the Paris Olympics with a game against Japan.
title: Paris Olympics: Brittney Griner is back

description: NPR's Ari Shapiro talks with Kamala Harris' childhood friend, Carole Porter, about how their upbringing in a redlined Bay Area neighborhood shaped Harris.
title: Kamala Harris' friend talks about how their childhood shaped her

description: Venezuela’s electoral authorities made it official: socialist President Nicolas Maduro will be in office for another six years. Opposition leaders are crying foul as small protests have broken out.
title: Venezuela's authoritarian leader claims victory, but opposition cries foul

description: The FBI says it's still working on its investigation into the attempted assassination of former President Donald Trump. The bureau has provided an update on what it has uncovered so far.
title: FBI says gunman’s actions show careful planning ahead of Trump rally

description: The Park Fire close to Chico, Calif., is now the largest in the U.S. On Monday, a man who was arrested under suspicion of starting the blaze is set to be arraigned.
title: The latest on the massive Park Fire — and the man arrested for allegedly starting it

description: The musician died this month at age 58. His collaborators are paying tribute to "a great artist who belongs to the world.”
title: Toumani Diabaté plucked the kora's 21 strings. The world fell in love with his music

description: A rocket struck a soccer field near the Lebanon border this weekend killing 12 children and wounding more. The community hit is Druze and, though Arab, can claim Israeli citizenship.
title: As the Druze in the Golan Height mourn, they question their relationship with Israel

description: The U.S. hadn't won an Olympic team medal in men's gymnastics since 2008. With a nearly flawless and gutsy performance Monday night, the boys are back on the podium in Paris.
title: U.S. men's gymnastics team breaks 16-year Olympic drought with a team bronze

description: McDonald's announced a drop in sales for the first time since 2020, when restaurants closed because of the pandemic. This time, it's because people are feeling the pinch of inflation.
title: McDonald's is losing customers to inflation

description: Here are photos from the energized campaigns leading up to Sunday's Venezuelan election. Now, with both sides claiming victory, there's a sense of uncertainty.
title: Hope was in the air for Venezuela's election, but it ended in dispute and uncertainty

description: This is the second Olympics to feature surfing, but it’s the first time competitors are riding waves that are a matter of “life or death,” according to professional big wave surfer Garrett McNamara.
title: Tahiti’s waves are a matter of ‘life and death’ for Olympic surfers

description: British diver Tom Daley won silver in the men's synchronized 10-meter platform on Monday. Fans were eager to see him compete — and knit. He made a splash with his poolside hobby at the Tokyo Olympics.
title: Tom Daley wins a 5th Olympic medal. But fans adore him, and his knitting, win or lose

description: What other pair could turn a relatively straight-forward 6-1, 6-4 second-round match into a clinic of tennis brilliance?
title: Djokovic and Nadal treat Olympic fans to a scintillating, if short, match in Paris

description: Team USA leads for the most number of medals earned in the Paris Olympics so far. But the team is trailing behind China, Japan, South Korea and Australia for the most gold.
title: How is Team USA faring in the Olympics? Here's a medal count so far

description: Nicolas Maduro has been declared the winner in Venezuela's presidential election, but the opposition is claiming fraud. And, former President Trump is trying to regain the spotlight from Harris.
title: Fraud claims emerge in Venezuelan election. And, Trump hopes to regain the spotlight

description: Olympic athletes strive to win gold, silver and bronze medals. But there was a different prize when the games originated in Greece more than 2,700 years ago.
title: Olympic Prizes: How did we get to the 3 medals?

description: After a strike this weekend that killed 12 children in the Israeli-occupied Golan Heights, is an all out war between Israel and the Lebanese group Hezbollah likely?
title: Israel blames Hezbollah for a deadly rocket strike in the Golan Heights

description: NPR's Leila Fadel asks Elaine Kamarck, author of "Picking the Vice President," about the Harris campaign's search for a running mate.
title: With less than 100 days to Election Day, Harris must choose a running mate

description: Five years ago, Harris also said she’d ‘prosecute the case’ against Trump. This time around, it hits a bit differently.
title: Harris is leaning into her history as a prosecutor. It's not the first time

description: The president is also expected to call for a constitutional amendment that would limit the broad immunity presidents now enjoy after a recent Supreme Court decision.
title: Biden calls for term limits, enforceable ethics rules for Supreme Court justices

description: Three years after the collapse of a condo building in Florida, developers say a court decision may stop them from demolishing and replacing older residential  buildings.
title: A court decision worries developers eyeing Florida's aging condos

description: Many Jewish Israelis are looking for ways to leave the country after Oct. 7, saying they don't feel safe in Israel anymore and that their government has failed them.
title: Some Jewish Israelis are making the choice to leave Israel over the war in Gaza

description: The Winklevoss twins, crypto money and other interests are seeking to shape the Phoenix-area Democratic primary on Tuesday for a U.S. House seat.
title: Winklevoss twins and crypto ties seek to shape Arizona Democratic primary race

description: Israel blames Hezbollah for deadly rocket strike. Venezuela’s electoral authority declares President Maduro the winner of Sunday’s election. Donald Trump escalates his attacks against VP Harris.
title: Morning news brief

description: Early in life, the protein Reelin helps assemble the brain. Later on, it appears to protect the organ from Alzheimer’s and other threats to memory and thinking.
title: A protein called Reelin keeps popping up in brains that resist aging and Alzheimer’s

description: Both men brought an end to their presidencies by declining the nomination of their party for another term.
title: Biden's withdrawal from the race has echoes of LBJ

description: Every four years, the Olympics puts a spotlight on gymnastics. But for boys in many parts of the U.S., it’s hard to even find a place to learn the sport.
title: Boys gymnastics programs are hard to find. That affects the U.S. Olympic pipeline.

description: JD Vance is the first veteran of Iraq or Afghanistan to appear on a presidential ballot. But he isn’t a hawk; he leads a contingent of war veterans in the GOP who oppose U.S. military intervention overseas.
title: JD Vance and the Republican vets who think American should do less, not more, abroad

description: As the U.S. women's basketball team plays its Olympic opener against Japan, expectations are high. The U.S. has won the last 7 gold medals, and hasn’t lost at the Olympics in most players' lifetimes.
title: Undefeated at the Olympics since 1992, USA women's basketball seeks 8th straight gold

description: About 4,000 personnel are fighting the Park Fire, the biggest active blaze in the nation. With slightly cooler weather over the weekend, they were able to increase containment.
title: Firefighters are working around the clock to contain Northern California's Park Fire

description: Older adults are more likely to be misdiagnosed than other adults. Multiple conditions and medications can make it tricky. Geriatric  ERs are an answer to this problem and they are catching on.
title: Emergency Rooms for geriatrics are helping older patients get diagnosed accurately

description: Iowa's ban on nearly all abortions as early as six weeks of pregnancy takes effect on Monday. Iowa joins 17 other states that restrict abortions then or earlier.
title: Iowa's abortion ban law is about to go into effect

description:
NPR's Leila Fadel talks to Daniel Byman, senior fellow at the Center for Strategic and International Studies,
about the military case for Israel supporting a ceasefire.
title: The war against Hamas is taking a toll on Israel's economy and military

description: The opposition claimed an "overwhelming" victory over Maduro on Sunday, as U.S. Secretary of State Antony Blinken expressed "serious concerns that the result announced does not reflect the will or the votes of the Venezuelan people.”
title: Maduro is declared winner in Venezuela's presidential election as opposition claims it prevailed

description: Republican presidential nominee Donald Trump isn't shying away from attacking Kamala Harris, as her campaign has energized Democrats and taken the spotlight off the former president.
title: What’s changed for Trump's campaign since Harris emerged as a presidential candidate?

description: A county in Maryland says it's the first to make pickleball a varsity sport, and it's expanding the game to all of its schools.
title: A school system in Maryland is offering pickleball as a varsity sport

description: NPR's Steve Inskeep talks to Matt Pottinger, editor of "The Boiling Moat," about the U.S. protecting Taiwan from an ever-encroaching China. Pottinger is a former deputy national security adviser.
title: 'The Boiling Moat' argues U.S. should prepare to help Taiwan defend against China

description: Republican vice presidential nominee JD Vance served in the Marine Corps. But unlike many Republican war veterans, he is a leading voice against U.S. military intervention abroad.
title: Vance, unlike many GOP war veterans, is a leading voice against military intervention

description: A Missouri man who has served more than three decades in prison remains incarcerated even though a judge ruled that he’s not guilty of murder and should be released.
title: Missouri man remains in prison after the state's high court puts his release on hold

description: The pair made history, with Kiefer becoming the first American woman to earn two gold medals in individual foil. Scruggs became the first Black fencer to medal for the U.S. in an individual women's event.
title: US fencers Kiefer and Scruggs take gold and silver in women's individual foil
